          <td valign="top">

<span class="txth1">Buffer Menus : Add menus for the current buffer only.</span> 

<br>
<br>

<!-- karma table -->
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="1" bordercolor="#000066">
<tr>
  <td class="lightbg"><b>&nbsp;script karma&nbsp;</b></td>
  <td>
    Rating <b>9/6</b>,
    Downloaded by 1928  </td>
  <td class="lightbg">
  <b>&nbsp;Comments, bugs, improvements&nbsp;</b>
  </td>
  <td>
    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Script:246">Vim wiki</a>
  </td>  
</tr>
</table>
<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=14">Michael Geddes</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td>Adds menus for the current buffer.&nbsp;&nbsp; When you leave the buffer, they get removed, and when you go back in, they are added again.<br>It cannot be used effectively to replace a menu as it is not possible to find out what the mapping used to be (as for map commands), and therefore not possible to restore it (*sigh*)<br><br>This is taken from my 'buffoptions' script, and should be useful in enabling menus to be added to ftplugin scripts.<br><br>NOTE: When adding to ftplugin scripts make VERY sure that the menus only get added ONCE (reinclude protection is good here).<br><br>TODO: (Please email me to add to this list)<br>- Allow 'Unmenu' of individual menus<br><br><br>Usage -<br>:Bmenu[!] [&quot;&lt;silent&gt;&quot;] [&quot;&lt;unmenu&gt;&quot;|&quot;&lt;disable&gt;&quot;] [&lt;modes&gt;] [&lt;priority&gt;] &lt;Menuname&gt; &lt;Mapping&gt;<br> 		Add menus to different modes for the current buffer.&nbsp;&nbsp;(Bang is used to<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;specify 'noremenu')<br>:B[ivacn]menu[!][&quot;&lt;silent&gt;&quot;] [&quot;&lt;unmenu&gt;&quot;|&quot;&lt;disable&gt;&quot;]&nbsp;&nbsp;[&lt;priority&gt;] &lt;Menuname&gt; &lt;Mapping&gt;<br>	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Add menu for one mode (or 'a' for all modes) for the current buffer.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(Bang is used to specify 'noremenu')<br><br>B[ivacn]noremenu [&quot;&lt;silent&gt;&quot;] [&quot;&lt;unmenu&gt;&quot;|&quot;&lt;disable&gt;&quot;] [&lt;modes&gt;] [&lt;priority&gt;] &lt;Menuname&gt; &lt;Mapping&gt;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adds a 'norecursive' menu.<br><br>The above commands accept '&lt;silent&gt;' as a flag to do a silent mapping.<br>They also allow &lt;SID&gt; (providing you have done the &quot;exe FindBufferSID()&quot;<br>at the beginning of the script), and will expand &lt;leader&gt; and &lt;localleader&gt;<br>in menu names.<br><br>If g:buffermenu_use_disable is set to 1 then all buffermenus use<br>enable/disable to update the menus.&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherwise, they will use menu/unmenu.<br>To override for one menu only, use &lt;unmenu&gt; or &lt;disable&gt;<br><br><br>:Bunmenuall<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Remove all menus for the current buffer<br><br>BufferOneShot( &lt;ident&gt; )<br> 		Use this to make sure Bmenus only get added ONCE per buffer.<br> 		eg:<br> 		if BufferOneShot('MyProgram')<br> 			Bmenu 10.20 Test.Test iHello&lt;esc&gt;<br> 		endif<br> 		A buffer local-variable called b:buffer_oneshot_MyProgram will be<br> 		created (just in case you want to unlet it when testing).<br><br>exe FindBufferSID() <br>		:exe the result of this function when using &lt;SID&gt; in menu commands so that the correct<br>		function gets called.<br><br></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td>This should be used as a general plugin - dump it into the plugin directory.<br><br>(Without the s: and &lt;SID&gt; it should work for 5.6, 5.7 as well, sourced from your vimrc )</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

